      I'm a bit iffy since I dont work with computers much and i dont want to waste bunches of money breaking stuff for a computer that wont turn on. So tell me, how easy is it to build your first computer? And would it not be smart to build a good computer your first time around?(good as in AMD 1.7 Ghz 512 mb DDR RAM 128 MB Geforce graphics card, that type thing) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bpaladinsofnorrath.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=kamino>Kamino</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 41<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(6/25/02 12:30:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15901.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: OT: How easy is it to build your own computer?</span><hr size=1> Well you have to start sometime right?  :P  To tell you the truth, it's not very hard to build a pc if you know what you're doing.  If you've ever fiddled around inside the case before and know what does what, then i don't think you will have much trouble.<br>
