Also, check www.pricewatch.com for deals on CPU + mobo combos.  You can usually buy a case that was tested for that combo and buy the other components later.  Hope this has helped. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukrilin31.showPublicProfile?language=EN>krilin31</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wandering Knight</span><br>  Posts: 213<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(6/25/02 12:33:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15901.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://krilin31.homestead.com/files/blow_up.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: OT: How easy is it to build your own computer?</span><hr size=1> Building your computer is quite easy.  I built mine and it was loads of fun and stuff, but I would not recommend using bleeding edge parts for your first computer.  I had problems with my modem being detected and had to swap it in and out of all of my com ports and had to buy 2 new modems before one worked.  I had 3 DOA hard drives (DON'T EVER BUY A HARD DRIVE FROM SAMSUNG!!!!) and that was a big pain.  This was my first computer so I didn't go whole hog on the parts, I have a site that might help you find the best price and one where you can talk with people who can help you if you run into problems(they helped me out with mine in a couple spots)<br>
